IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: Tri-County United Way is an organization dedicated to helping people. We work to improve lives and make a positive impact in our communities by raising resources, both monetary and volunteer. We strive to do this through collaboration with others encouraging volunteerism and resolving community problems through identifying and communicating our community's priority issues.

IRS990.Desc: Community Services:Sponsors education, recreation, social and spiritual programs to all individuals and families withing the Tri-County area. Not-for-profit agencies served include Adirondack Samaritan counseling center, Adirondack vets house, caritas, inc., family service association, greater Adirondack home aides, greater glens falls senior citizens center, moreau community center, salvation army and the senior center of the Kingsbury fort Edward area, inc. See Schedule I or more details regarding agencies served.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: Special Education and Research: Provides special educational and research to aid professionals and the public, improve attitudes and services of its participants. Not-for-profit agencies served include catholic charities of Saratoga, warren and Washington counties, the aids council of neny, glens falls association for the blind, retired and senior volunteer program, and literacy neny. See Schedule I for more details regarding these agencies served.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: To promote volunteerism within the community and maintain an office to match volunteers with organizations in need of assistance. To provide tax preparation and filing assistance to low to moderate income individuals and families during the first quarter of the calendar year. Partnered with the IRS to operate a volunteer income tax assistance (VITA) site in Queensbury, NY, Back Pack Program to provide weekend meals to area children and scholarships to area high school graduates.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: In accordance with generally accepted accounting principles, the Organization accounts for uncertainty in income taxes by recognizing tax positions in the financial statements when it is more-likely-than-not the positions will be sustained upon examination by tax authorities. As of June 30, 2022, the Organization believes that it has appropriate support for the income tax positions taken on its tax returns and, therefore, believes that it has no uncertain tax positions that would have a material impact on the financial statements. As of June 30, 2022, the tax years that remain subject to examination by taxing authorities begin with 2019.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Grantmaker's Description of How Grants are Used
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The use of grant funds is annually monitored by the organization as a part of the community investment process. When an agency submits a request for funds, a financial review of the agency is required.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part III, Line 4d: Other Program Services Description
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: OTHER PROGRAM SERVICES 4: To promote volunteerism within the community and maintain an office to match volunteers with organizations in need of assistance. SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 11b: Form 990 Review Process
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Tax returns are reviewed by the finance committee and the board of directors prior to signature and submission.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 12c: Explanation of Monitoring and Enforcement of Conflicts
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The organization has a conflict of interest policy that is monitored and updated on a regular basis. THe organization also has an ethics officer who is responsible for monitoring and enforcing compliance with the policy.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 15a: Compensation Review & Approval Process - CEO, Top Management
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The compensation review and approval process for all executive positions is performed on an annual basis by the board of directors and executive committee. A strategic measurement process is discussed and planned by the chairman of the board and is reviewed by the board of directors.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 19: Other Organization Documents Publicly Available
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Governing documents, conflict of interest policies and financial statements are made available to the public upon request.
